{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/bbc-sports-air-application-removes-its-offensive-language/","result":{"data":{"site":{"id":"Site","siteMetadata":{"title":"James Ford","author":"James Ford"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"724323b1-27ae-5b1a-a89f-eacacf27e6fe","html":"<p>Well, that was fast (and rightly so).  This morning I posted about the <a href=\"http://www.psyked.co.uk/adobe/apollo/bbc-uses-air-to-install-a-list-of-swear-words-to-users-machines.htm\">BBC Sports' Olympics AIR Application containing a text file of offensive language</a> but now, roughly 1.5 hours after posting here, and 6.5 hours after it being initally posted, a new update has appeared for the Olympics AIR Application.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 500px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/41099/bbc-fixed.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"bbc fixed\"\n        title=\"bbc fixed\"\n        src=\"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/41099/bbc-fixed.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/f93b5/bbc-fixed.jpg 300w,\n/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/41099/bbc-fixed.jpg 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The release notes mention that it's updating the listing events schedule (which it may well be) but it's also changing the contents of the <strong>bbc-swear.txt</strong> file to say '<strong>deprecated functionality</strong>'. (Instead of 1399 ways to swear.)</p>\n<p>Our experence is that the auto-updater appears a little buggy - clicking update seems to start a background download process, and the installer kicks in when the application is fully downloaded.  Unfortunately without a progress indicator, it seems that things just aren't working.  Nevertheless, a little patience and your application should launch the built in Adobe AIR installer soon enough.</p>\n<p>Fast (frantic?) work from the BBC!</p>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"title":"BBC Sports' AIR Application removes its offensive language","date":"August 05, 2008","tags":["air","auto-updating","bbc","olympics","swearing"],"url":null,"image":{"id":"af76dd03-d9ad-578f-a815-7f7b63faf879","childImageSharp":{"id":"8bc53d34-7577-5d2c-a12c-a465939485e8","sizes":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7857142857142858,"src":"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/0f3a1/bbc-fixed.jpg","srcSet":"/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/426bb/bbc-fixed.jpg 158w,\n/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/6544a/bbc-fixed.jpg 315w,\n/static/adb351016b45ac91d45a568b990934a7/0f3a1/bbc-fixed.jpg 500w","sizes":"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"}},"colors":{"vibrant":"#8CD404","darkVibrant":"#68AA04","lightVibrant":"#638FC4","muted":"#8A9979","darkMuted":"#26444E","lightMuted":"#BCC9DA"}},"description":null,"image_credit":null}}},"pageContext":{"prev":{"frontmatter":{"path":"/blog/bbc-uses-air-to-install-a-list-of-swear-words-to-users-machines/","tags":["bbc","olypmics","swearing"],"title":"BBC uses Adobe AIR to install a list of swear words to users machines.","date":"2008-08-05T09:01:35.000Z","description":null,"image":{"childImageSharp":{"sizes":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7857142857142858,"src":"/static/e9e611abe55649998a5d68184c61fa63/0f3a1/bbc-swear.jpg